<span style="text-align: center; color:green; font-size:30px;">About Us </span>
<span style=" color:rgb(102,51,0); font-size:18px;">

The Take Care Organization (TCO) is one of the largest independent disease awareness organization in India. It was founded in 2004 to give victims and concerned citizens a united voice, to raise public awareness about the most serious disease and to work towards a common goal. TCO is dedicated to preventing diseases through national and international education, advocacy, and community initiatives.
 
<span style="text-align: center; color:green; font-size:25px;">TCO’s Goals</span>
<ul>
	<li> <span style="text-align: center; color:green; font-size:20px;">Education.</span> Educate the public and medical community the causes, treatments  and medical resources of the diseases. Support research that leads to early detection, prevention and a cure.
<li> <span style="text-align: center; color:green; font-size:20px;">	Advocacy.</span> Collaborate with organizations around the world for a global financial support to the patients. Raise awareness to Protect victims’.
<li> <span style="text-align: center; color:green; font-size:20px;">	Community.</span>  Unite victims to Share Their Stories, learn about treatment options, and support each other.<br><br></ul>

